This project uses Zero Point Coder (ZPC) for persistent memory.

## Session Start

Run `agent-do zpc status` to see memory state.
Run `agent-do zpc patterns` to review established conventions.

## Capture Lessons

When errors resolve, corrections occur, or conventions are discovered:

```bash
agent-do zpc learn "context" "problem" "solution" "takeaway" --tags "tag1,tag2"
```

## Log Decisions

For architectural choices:

```bash
agent-do zpc decide "problem" --options "a,b,c" --chosen "b" --rationale "why" --confidence 0.8
```

Check existing decisions first: `agent-do zpc query --type decisions`

## Consolidation

Run `agent-do zpc harvest` after significant work to consolidate lessons into patterns.

## Agent Completion

Before reporting done:
1. Log error-resolution pairs via `agent-do zpc learn`
2. Log decisions via `agent-do zpc decide`
3. Include: "Lessons logged: N (new) | Decisions logged: N (new)"
